<div id="box5">
<h1>Basic Information</h1>
<b>Name:</b> X<br>
<b>Pronunciation:</b> Key<br>
<b>Age:</b> Ageless. Appears around early twenties.<br>
<b>Gender:</b> Female<br>
<b>Sexuality:</b> Demisexual<br>
<b>Species:</b> Dimensional Guardian<br>
<b>Race:</b> Will-o-the-Wisp<br>
<b>Talents:</b> Singing, Dancing<br>
<b>Instruments:</b> Vocal, Ocarina<br>
<b>Occupation:</b> Teacher at <a href="http://ulreich.weebly.com">Ulreich University</a><br>
<b>Magic Trees:</b> Faith, Spiritualism<br>
<b>Rank:</b> High Mage, Mage<br>
<b>Points:</b> 25<br>
<b>Height:</b> 5'6"<br>
<b>Weight:</b> 120 lbs.
</div>
</div>

<div id="tab1">
<h1>Detailed Information</h1>
<b>Appearance</b><br>
In the sunlight, X has a tangible humanoid body. She is thin and fragile to the naked eye with very pale skin and very long stark white hair. While her hourglass figure and feminine body parts are fairly curvy, she weighs no more than one-hundred-twenty pounds. Her facial structure is very elegant in nature, with strong high cheekbones, elvish style pointed ears, tiny slightly upturned button nose, and full soft pink lips. Her wide eyes stand out while almost blending in; her irises the palest shade of liquid silver, bright enough to stand out against the whites of her eyes but blend in with the rest of her appearance.<br><br>
In the moonlight and the darkness of the night, her true appearance shines through. She is nothing more than an embodiment of pale creamy blue--almost white--energy and is often mistaken for a ghost or a spirit. She keeps the same silhouette she has during the day but now weighs nothing more than a feather and is not tangible by normal means.
<br><br>
<b>Personality</b><br>
She is a very nuetral person with her own set of morals and beliefs. While she is kind, caring, loyal, and loving to the people, places, and things that find themselves in her favor, she is very cold, crude, and violent toward the things that don't. Most often she finds herself in controversies she doesn't wish to have thanks to her neutral standpoint; if it doesn't benefit her, she sees no need to pursue it.
</div>

<div id="tab2">
<img style="width:100%;margin-top:8%;border-radius:20%;" src="http://i.imgur.com/BqnGKr2.png"/>
</div>

<div id="tab3">
<h1>The Birth of "X"</h1>
There is a spiritual being that exists between the realms of the living and the dead, the mortal and the supernatural. This creature is known simply as a key. Its origins aren't fully known, but research and comparison between all forms of lore in which it reveals itself, has given us the ability to piece together and theorize where it all began. 
<br><br>
We believe that in the beginning when the worlds were formed, there was no line to separate life from death, beginnings and ends. Any beings that lived at the time passed between possibilities and true free will was accessible to anyone and everyone. For awhile, this worked out very well and all the beings lived in peace with each other, until greed and lust for power overcame them and they began killing each other off.
<br><br>
The higher beings--perhaps fate and destiny themselves--decided it was time to draw lines between the realms to limit the powers of all future existences. These lines have become what we know now as the divides between dimensions. Once again there was a peace, but it was short lived. The inhabitants of each dimension soon learned how to bypass the divides and cast wars on each other across the worlds, so the higher beings once again interfered. They created a new race to live and thrive within the divides to guard the pathways between.
<br><br>
Even these beings, however, would soon learn about power and develop their own motives. So the higher powers banded together to make another higher being to sit as a lawmaker, a monarchy--an oracle if you will--to rule over the guardians of the divide. They granted this new higher being special abilities and named her "X."
<br><br>
This is what we believe to be the origin of the creature you are here to meet.<br><br>

<h1>Will-o'-the-Wisps</h1>
The "Will-O'-The-Wisps"--Wisps to shorten that up--were the guardians the higher beings created to live within the divide. 
<br><br>
Small orbs of aura-like energy that glow in the darkness and fade in the light. They are simple spirits that communicate through movement and color. Wisps can come in almost every color out there, their color allows them to recognize each other's jobs in their simple society. 
<br><br>
They each have been granted knowledge but cannot communicate by word-of-mouth. Throughout the earlier mentioned lore it has been revealed that if one desires to learn the knowledge a Wisp has appeared to give them, they must simply follow the creature. This simple fact has dubbed the guardians the "Guides of Destiny" or "Guides of Knowledge" in multiple cultures. 
<br><br>
Wisps do have a language, but they can only speak among their own kind. Well, I suppose they could speak anywhere really but can only be heard by their own. They have a fascinating method of speech. They spread sound waves by quickly flickering their auras. To any other ear it would sound like the snapping of fingers or the crackling of a flame, but to each other every flicker unlocks a whole new language.
<br><br>
Wisps are not bound by morals, but simple laws set by their queen. They will lead someone to further knowledge or even death without a second thought and lack the capabilities for emotional attachments. They are motivated by one thing, and one thing only: obey the queen.
</div>

<div id="tab4">
<img style="height:100%;margin-left:8%;" src="http://i.imgur.com/GyPqSyb.png"/>
</div>

<div id="tab5">
<h1>The Powers of a Wisp Queen</h1>
<b>Passing Days</b><br>
Day and night, sun and moon, no longer affect whether or not X has a physical form or an ethereal form. While her ethereal form is still attainable and still very weak and vulnerable to magic, she can now choose whether she will take on her physical humanoid form or her spiritual one. Her ethereal form is still how she regenerates energy and regains the health she needs to stay alive, so she cannot go without taking this form for long periods of time. <br><br>
<b>Self Healing</b><br>
If X is hurt by natural means ONLY--in other words, is not hurt with magic but gets the flu or is stabbed with a knife by a non-mage human or a non-enchanted weapon--when she changes into her pure energy form at night the injuries and illnesses no longer remain and the next morning her human body is as good as new.<br><br>
<b>Mana Sensitivity</b><br>
Wisps are sensitive to other beings who use mana. While they cannot sense specifics, the use of mana in an area can leave behind a detectable imprint allowing them to track much like a dog does with a scent.<br><br>
<b>Tireless</b><br>
Wisps do not need sleep to regenerate, just being in their spirit forms allows them to regenerate energy healthily--only as much energy as sleep would regenerate for a human--and do not need to eat unless they are exerting excess energy while in their human forms. <br><br>
<b>Ageless</b><br>
A Wisp chooses which human-equivalent age they wish to stay and stop physically and mentally aging once they reach that point. This is why Wisps are often depicted as children--many wish to stay young and innocent. X herself chose the age of 24. 
<h1>Universal Spells</h1>
<b>Aura</b><br>
Every living thing has mana, and the colors of their mana and their aura vary from person to person. X's mana is always a very pale blue color, but varies in its shades depending on her mood.
<i>"Light (sky) blue: peace, serenity, ethereal, spiritual, infinity 
(The origin of these meanings is the intangible aspects of the sky.)" </i><br>
Of all universal auras, there are a standard three that have been taught to mages for hundreds of years: A Utility Aura, an Offensive Aura, and a Defensive Aura. <br>
<b>Utility Aura</b><br>
Cast by concentrating on the mind itself, both in a figurative and literal sense. Casters will start by weaving mana directly into their brains, allowing the aura to expand throughout their entire body, flowing directly from the top of their heads. The aura will take a very liquid-like appearance while this spell is cast, flowing downwards over the body in a smooth, gentle motion. The aura will glow lightly, being slightly visible in direct light, but bright enough to glow during the darkness. With the aura up, it increases a being's reflexes and overall agility. The aura will make a person feel extremely awake and alert, and increase their visual perception slightly. This aura will last for a period of four posts, and can be upheld for another four by charging it with mana (expending the cost to bring it up over again). 
<br>
<b>Defensive Aura</b><br>
Cast by concentrating on the very thing that keeps you standing. In most cases, this means the caster must begin by weaving mana directly into their spine, and allow it to flow into the rest of their body. This aura takes an extremely solid and rigid appearance; it will form around your entire body like a suit of armor, and does not contain an ethereal glow, rather a shine very similar to polished metal. The spine itself will glow slightly, and pulse, causing energy to run throughout the aura. Takes two turns to cast (one turn to prepare weaving mana into the epicenter, and one post allowing the aura to fully take effect). With the aura up, it is able to provide a x1.5 defense against physical based attacks (both natural and physical mana) as well as a x1.25 defense against energy based attacks. While this aura is active, the user will become more heavy and grounded, making it much harder to stagger or knock them down. As an added bonus, the casters pain tolerance increases significantly. This aura will last for a period of four posts, and can be upheld for another four by charging it with mana (expending the cost to bring it up over again). 
<br>
<b>Offensive Aura</b><br>
Cast by concentrating your focus toward the very thing that gives you life. Although various creatures have vital organs in different areas, the most common place for the aura to originate from is the chest, directly in the center. For humans and other similar beings, the heart itself acts as the conduit. The caster must weave mana directly into this organ (or simply a space on the front of their chest) and allow it to spread throughout their entire body. This aura is extremely volatile in nature, and appears very similar to flames covering the beings entirety, crackling and flaring haphazardly around them.Takes two turns to cast (one turn to prepare weaving mana into the epicenter, and one post allowing the aura to fully take effect). With the aura up, it is able to provide a slight boost (x1.5) to a person's physical strength, as well as their casting speed (this does not work for spells that require multiple posts to charge), and spell damage (around x1.25 more power, does not increase the rank of spells). The aura will make a person feel extremely warm and accelerated, creatures who possess hearts and similar organs will find that they will beat extremely fast while the aura is up. This aura will last for a period of four psts, and can be upheld for another four by charging it with mana (expending the cost to bring it up over again). 
<br><br>
<b>Mana Weave</b><br>
The simple act of moving one's mana pool through their own body. Channeling one's mana. 
<br><br>
<b>Mana Spark</b><br>
Basic mana projectile that can be used offensively or defensively.<br><br>
<b>Mana Target</b><br>
A small dot of mana that acts as a guide for one's magic. Wherever this target is placed, no matter where or what direction the spell is cast, it will hit the Mana Target.<br><br>
<b>Mana Beacon</b><br>
A strong burst of mana used like a distress signal. Nearby mages can feel the beacon and will come to aid the caster.
</div>

