<div id="tab7">
<h1>Spiritual Ease; Archmage</h1>
<b>Call of the Living</b><br>
Congratulations, X has finally obtained the ability to revive students, now that she can combine aspects of both Faith and Spiritualism together into a whole new Tree! When a student's body is no longer capable of holding its spirit--basically they die--then X can weave her mana into the corpse. This act allows her to read everything she can about the passed on mage's identity, and collect all the information she needs to not only heal the body so it can live again, but also know which spirit in the vast number to call. After summoning the spirit belonging to the body back to where its dead flesh remains and giving it the choice to stay dead or return to life, she will then begin renewing the connection between both entities by healing the body so the spirit may successfully inhabit it once more!<br><br>
<b>Diamond Rush</b><br>
X creates a basketball sized hollow orb. Don't let this fact, and the fact that it is translucent and looks very much like glass, fool you. The walls of this sphere are strong barriers made by an archmage Faith spell. When the surface of these orbs are hit by magical, physical, or even spiritual based attacks, the attack will just be reflected back. These orbs can be manipulated by X telepathically for a ten foot radius around her body, are as tough as Tungsten, can be charged up to be used like projectiles, and can reach speeds of up to 120 MPH maximum. The orb itself isn't the cause for concern, however, it is what is inside the orb. When forming Diamond Rush, X must first ask spirits for favors: if they would lend themselves to be temporarily enclosed in these orbs. These spirits are all toxic based, and if they agree to be enclosed inside and the orb is broken, a thick smog of green haze will explode from within and spread around naturally in the air like gas. Inhaling this smog will cause a fast deterioration of the lungs and great discomfort in the throat. X can have up to four Diamond Rush orbs summoned at once.<br><br>
<b>Shooting Star</b><br>
When casting this spell, a soft glitter-like substance will fall like rain from ten feet above ground. This "rain" has two modes, the first being a Faith spell. Mages affected by the Faith mode, will have minor wounds quickly healed, and more major wounds if they stay under the spell for long enough time. Mages affected by the Spiritualism mode will be greeted with icy shards of Spirit Force. These shards are cold enough to cause burning of the skin if a mage is under the glitter for long enough. X is not only able to pick and choose which mages within the radius are affected by this spell, but she can also use both modes simultaneously for a much higher mana cost.

<h1>Faith; Archmage</h1>
<b>Repair</b><br>
A simple spell that allows X to mend wounds in any organic substance.<br><br>
<b>Cleanse</b><br>
A spell that allows X to cleanse infected organic material. Infections that can be cleansed are physical or magical--like deceptions, hexes, and hostile mana--as long as they're the same rank or below her.<br><br>
<b>Wall</b><br>
A magic shield of mana that can reflect attacks from mages the same rank as X herself or lower back in the original direction of trajectory. While it can vary in size, the biggest she can possibly make this wall is only two feet above her head and in a five foot radius around her body.<br><br>
<b>Warrior's Blessing</b><br>
A spell that acts as a boost. This spell allows other mages a slight boost in physical strength. Cannot be cast on herself.<br><br>
<b>Athlete's Blessing</b><br>
Another boost spell. This spell allows other mages a slight boost in physical endurance. Cannot be cast on herself.<br><br>
<b>Renew</b><br>
If an organic substance is missing parts of its original whole body (i.e. a human missing an arm or leg) then this spell allows X to regenerate an entire section of that organic body that is missing. This also goes for internal organic material (such as broken bones being healed/mended).<br><br>
<b>Tension Reliever</b><br>
If this spell is being cast, a gentle refreshing mist will form, thick enough to cause a slight disruption of sight, but not enough to cause any trouble or confusion. The spell merely acts as a calming agent, loosening tightened muscles, lowering adrenaline levels slightly, and calming nerves. The spell works primarily on the specific person it's being cast on, but if others are present they can be slightly affected by the spell. Any Deception Magic or Curses of equal rank to her or lower will be broken off of whomever this spell is cast on.<br><br>

<h1>Spiritualism; Mage</h1>
<b>Communication</b><br>
The simple ability to see and talk with spirits who do not have tangible forms.<br><br>
<b>Summon</b><br>
The ability given to all Spiritualism mages that allows them to summon spirits to aide them.<br><br>
<b>Healing Contract:</b><br>
X contacts a spirit and asks them to look inside an injured person for her. This spirit can tell her what kind of unseen damage has been done to their organic body.
<br><br>
<b>Soul Cleanse</b><br>
Finally X has achieved high enough rank in Spiritualism to experience the wonders of Spirit Force! This spell allows her to cleanse any damage done to sentient things on a spiritual level rather than physical. So long as the cause of the damage was the same rank as her or lower. (This must be done via communicating with spirits and asking them to lend their purifying force. One charge cast up, next post puts spell into effect.)
<br><br>
<b>Pulse Diagram</b><br>
This spell allows her to see the internal functions and status of any organic body so long as she weaves her mana through them. (The diagram X recieves in her mind is completely sonar, much akin to giving an ultrasound.)
<br><br>
<b>Thermal Redact</b><br>
X makes a request of an ice spirit, if they agree they will very slowly absorb all the thermal energy within a ten foot radius. (One post charge up, second post makes spell effective.)
<br><br>
<b>Flash Bang</b><br>
Another request from a spirit, this spirit calls on the power of photokinetics to burst into a bright flash of light that would temporarily blind the average human for about five seconds. 
<br><br>
<b>Hidden</b><br>
X requests of a spirit to use its powers to hide something within itself, meaning only specific mages of any rank would be able to see what is hidden. (Spiritualists, Necromancers, and any mage one rank higher than X with sensory abilities. First post charges, second post casts. )
</div>

